Préambule¶

1) Présentation du sujet¶

Notre objectif est raliser une segmentation des clients du site de vente en ligne Olist. Les donnes rcupres sont spares en 9 fichiers que nous analyserons succintement avant de les regrouper. Nous utiliserons ensuite ces donnes aggrges ultrieurement afin de proposer diffrents modles de segmentation.

# Graphique en camembert
def distribution_variables_object3(variable,x,y,titre,coupe=None):
    vect_description=variable.value_counts(normalize=True)
    if coupe is not None :
        vect_description_new= vect_description[vect_description>coupe]
        d={'autres':1-vect_description_new.sum()}
        ser=pd.Series(d,copy=False)
        vect_description_new=vect_description_new.append(ser)
        print(vect_description_new.head(10))
        
        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(x,y))
        ax = fig.add_axes([0,0,1,1])
        ax.axis('equal')
        ax.pie(vect_description_new, labels = vect_description_new.index) 
               #autopct='%1.2f%%')
    else :
        print(vect_description.head(20))
        # depicting the visualization
        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(x,y))
        ax = fig.add_axes([0,0,1,1])
        ax.axis('equal')
        ax.pie(vect_description, labels = vect_description.index)
               #autopct='%1.2f%%')
  
    # displaying the title
    plt.title(label=titre,
          
          fontstyle='italic')
  

    plt.show()

# Diagramme en barre
def distribution_variables_object4(variable,x,y,titre,coupe):
    vect_description=variable.value_counts(normalize=True)
    vect_description_new= vect_description[vect_description>coupe]
    d={'autres':1-vect_description_new.sum()}
    ser=pd.Series(d,copy=False)
    vect_description_new=vect_description_new.append(ser)
    vect_description_new.head(9).plot(kind='barh',figsize=(x,y))
    plt.title(label= titre)
    plt.show()

def missing_values_barplot(dataset):
    missing_values = dataset.isnull().sum()
    plt.figure(figsize=(20,10))
    plt.title("Pourcentages de valeurs manquantes par variable")
    plt.xlabel("Variables")
    plt.ylabel("Pourcentages de valeurs manquantes")
    plt.bar(np.arange(missing_values.index.size),
            100 * missing_values / dataset.index.size,
            color='b', width=1, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xticks(np.arange(missing_values.index.size),
               missing_values.index,
               rotation=90)

def haversine_np(lon1, lat1, lon2, lat2):
    lat1 = lat1 * math.pi / 180.0
    lat2 = lat2 * math.pi / 180.0
    dLat = (lat2 - lat1)
    dLon = (lon2 - lon1) * math.pi / 180.0
    a =dLat.apply(lambda x: pow(np.sin(x / 2), 2))
    b =dLon.apply(lambda x: pow(np.sin(x / 2), 2))                      
    c =a+b*lat1.apply(lambda x: np.cos(x)) * lat2.apply(lambda x: np.cos(x))
    r = 6371
    d = 2 * c.apply(lambda x: np.arcsin(np.sqrt(x)))
    e=r*d
    return e

                    -df_synt['order_purchase_timestamp'].dt.date).dt.days

                                     - df_synt['order_purchase_timestamp'].dt.date).dt.days

                                                -df_synt['order_purchase_timestamp'].dt.date).dt.days
df_synt['delta_order_delivered_customer_date']= (df_synt['order_delivered_customer_date'].dt.date
                                                -df_synt['order_purchase_timestamp'].dt.date).dt.days
df_synt['differentiel_date_prevue']= (df_synt['order_estimated_delivery_date'].dt.date
                                     -df_synt['order_delivered_customer_date'].dt.date).dt.days
df_synt['delta_seller_to_carrier_status'] = (df_synt['shipping_limit_date'].dt.date 
                                            -df_synt['order_delivered_carrier_date'].dt.date).dt.days

#Classification des produits 
def classify_cat(x):

    if x in ['office_furniture', 'furniture_decor',
             'furniture_living_room', 'kitchen_dining_laundry_garden_furniture',
             'bed_bath_table', 'home_comfort', 'home_comfort_2',
             'home_construction', 'garden_tools', 'furniture_bedroom',
             'furniture_mattress_and_upholstery']:
        return 'Furniture'
    
    elif x in ['auto', 'computers_accessories',
               'musical_instruments', 'consoles_games',
               'watches_gifts', 'air_conditioning',
               'telephony', 'electronics',
               'fixed_telephony', 'tablets_printing_image',
               'computers', 'small_appliances_home_oven_and_coffee',
               'small_appliances', 'audio', 'signaling_and_security', 'security_and_services']:
        return 'Electronics'
    
    elif x in ['fashio_female_clothing', 'fashion_male_clothing', 'fashion_bags_accessories',
               'fashion_shoes', 'fashion_sport', 'fashion_underwear_beach',
               'fashion_childrens_clothes', 'baby', 'cool_stuff', ]:
        return 'Fashion'
    
    elif x in ['housewares', 'home_confort', 'home_appliances',
               'home_appliances_2', 'flowers', 'costruction_tools_garden',
               'garden_tools', 'construction_tools_lights', 'costruction_tools_tools',
               'luggage_accessories', 'la_cuisine', 'pet_shop', 'market_place']:
        return 'Home & Garden'
    
    elif x in ['sports_leisure', 'toys', 'cds_dvds_musicals',
               'music', 'dvds_blu_ray', 'cine_photo',
               'party_supplies', 'christmas_supplies', 'arts_and_craftmanship', 'art']:
        return 'Entertainment'
    
    elif x in ['health_beauty', 'perfumery', 'diapers_and_hygiene']:
        return 'Beauty & Health'
    
    elif x in ['food_drink', 'drinks', 'food']:
        return 'Food & Drinks'
    
    elif x in ['books_general_interest', 'books_technical', 'books_imported', 'stationery']:
        return 'Books & Stationery'
    
    elif x in ['construction_tools_construction', 'construction_tools_safety',
               'industry_commerce_and_business', 'agro_industry_and_commerce']:
        return 'Industry & Construction'

df_synt['product_category'] = df_synt['product_category_name_english'].apply(classify_cat)

def boxplotdistandlog(variable,a,b):
    f, ax = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize = (a,b), gridspec_kw = {"height_ratios": (.15, .85)})
   
    sns.boxplot(variable, ax = ax[0, 0], orient = "h")
    ax[0, 0].set(xlabel='')
    ax[0, 0].set_title("")
    sns.histplot(variable, ax = ax[1, 0])
    ax[1, 0].set(xlabel='')
   
    variable_log = np.log(variable + 1)
    sns.boxplot(variable_log, ax = ax[0, 1], orient = "h")
    ax[0, 1].set(xlabel='')
    ax[0, 1].set_title("")
    sns.histplot(variable_log, ax = ax[1, 1])
    ax[1, 1].set(xlabel='')
    
   
    plt.show()
    print("coefficient d'asymtrie:", variable.skew())
    print("coefficient d'asymtrie aprs transformation:", np.log(variable+1).skew())
